# ResQConnect API request samples
#
# This file can be used with REST clients that understand the ``.http`` format
# (VS Code REST Client extension, JetBrains HTTP client, etc.).
# Update the ``baseUrl`` variable below to point at your running backend
# instance, then execute the desired request block.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@authToken = {{YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN_HERE}}

### Chatbot: Generate a response
POST {{baseUrl}}/chatbot/ask
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "prompt": "Provide evacuation guidance for a coastal flood affecting downtown.",
  "chat_history": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the current flood status in the bay area?"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The bay is experiencing moderate flooding with road closures near the docks."
    }
  ],
  "user": {
    "id": "responder-42",
    "name": "Alex Morgan",
    "role": "Logistics Coordinator",
    "location": {
      "latitude": 37.8044,
      "longitude": -122.2712
    }
  }
}

### Template: Generic GET request
# Duplicate this block and adjust the HTTP method, path, and headers
# to exercise other endpoints exposed by the backend.
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Template: Generic JSON POST request
# Replace ``/path`` and the body with endpoint-specific values when testing.
POST {{baseUrl}}/path
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "example": "value"
}
